lready registered. Please check linkage and avoid linking the same target more than once.\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Libraries imported successfully!\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":1},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Data Loading and Organization\nRetrieving the image paths from the directories.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n# Defining the exact data directory based on your Kaggle dataset\ndata_dir = '/kaggle/input/datasets/ninadaithal/imagesoasis/Data'\n\n# Function to list image paths\ndef get_image_paths(directory):\n    return [os.path.join(directory, f) for f in os.listdir(directory) if f.endswith('.jpg')]\n\nprint(\"Loading all image paths\")\n# Loading all paths for each category\nnon_demented_all = get_image_paths(os.path.join(data_dir, 'Non Demented'))\nvery_mild_all = get_image_paths(os.path.join(data_dir, 'Very mild Dementia'))\nmild_all = get_image_paths(os.path.join(data_dir, 'Mild Dementia'))\nmoderate_all = get_image_paths(os.path.join(data_dir, 'Moderate Dementia'))\n\nprint(\"Splitting data into train (80%) and test (20%) sets\")\n# Automatically splitting the data\nnon_demented_train, non_demented_test = train_test_split(non_demented_all, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\nvery_mild_demented_train, very_mild_demented_test = train_test_split(very_mild_all, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\nmild_demented_train, mild_demented_test = train_test_split(mild_all, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\nmoderate_demented_train, moderate_demented_test = train_test_split(moderate_all, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\n\nprint(\"Image paths loaded and split successfully\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-06T16:04:05.262460Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-06T16:04:05.262982Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.836124Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-06T16:04:05.262955Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.835328Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Loading all image paths\nSplitting data into train (80%) and test (20%) sets\nImage paths loaded and split successfully\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":2},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Step 1 of Hierarchical Approach: Healthy vs. Sick\nHere lies our main modification: we merge the \"Very Mild\", \"Mild\", and \"Moderate\" stages into a single \"Sick\" category (Label 1). Healthy brains (\"Non Demented\") keep Label 0. \nWe also apply undersampling to avoid RAM saturation.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n# 1. Merge the 3 sick stages into one large \"Sick\" category\ndemented_train = very_mild_demented_train + mild_demented_train + moderate_demented_train\ndemented_test = very_mild_demented_test + mild_demented_test + moderate_demented_test\n\n# 2. Limit the size for memory constraints (here 800 images per class)\ntarget_train = 800\nnon_demented_train_samp = random.sample(non_demented_train, k=target_train)\ndemented_train_samp = random.sample(demented_train, k=target_train)\n\n# Do the same for the test set (here 100 images per class)\ntarget_test = 100\nnon_demented_test_samp = random.sample(non_demented_test, k=target_test)\ndemented_test_samp = random.sample(demented_test, k=target_test)\n\n# 3. Create DataFrames (0 = healthy, 1 = sick)\ntrain_df = pd.DataFrame({\n    'path': non_demented_train_samp + demented_train_samp,\n    'label': [0] * target_train + [1] * target_train\n})\n\ntest_df = pd.DataFrame({\n    'path': non_demented_test_samp + demented_test_samp,\n    'label': [0] * target_test + [1] * target_test\n})\n\n# Shuffle the training and test sets\ntrain_df = train_df.sample(frac=1, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)\ntest_df = test_df.sample(frac=1, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)\n\nprint(f\"Training dataset ready: {len(train_df)} images.\")\nprint(f\"Testing dataset ready: {len(test_df)} images.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.837074Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.837417Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.855760Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.837392Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.854833Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Training dataset ready: 1600 images.\nTesting dataset ready: 200 images.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Image Preprocessing\nWe use the original function to load the physical images into memory, resize them to 128x128, and normalize the pixels to be between 0 and 1.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\ndef load_images(df, img_size=(128, 128)):\n    images = []\n    labels = df['label'].values\n    for path in df['path']:\n        img = cv2.imread(path)\n        img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB) # Convert to RGB\n        img = cv2.resize(img, img_size)\n        images.append(img)\n    return np.array(images), np.array(labels)\n\nprint(\"Loading images\")\nX_train, y_train = load_images(train_df)\nX_test, y_test = load_images(test_df)\n\n# Normalize pixels (between 0 and 1)\nX_train = X_train / 255.0\nX_test = X_test / 255.0\n\nprint(\"Images loaded and normalized successfully\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.856904Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.857738Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-06T16:04:22.032733Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-06T16:04:06.857698Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-06T16:04:22.031738Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Loading images\nImages loaded and normalized successfully\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Modeling: EfficientNetB0 (Binary Classification)\nUse of the original architecture based on the pre-trained EfficientNetB0 model (Transfer Learning).\n**Crucial Modification:** The final `Dense` layer is changed from 4 to 2 neurons, because we are now performing a binary classification (healthy vs. sick).","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n# Load the pre-trained model without the final classification layer\nbase_model = EfficientNetB0(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(128, 128, 3))\n\n# Build the final architecture\nmodel = Sequential([\n    base_model,\n    GlobalAveragePooling2D(),\n    BatchNormalization(),\n    Dropout(0.5),\n    Dense(2, activation='softmax') #change from 4 to 2 outputs\n])\n\n# Compilation of the model\nmodel.compile(optimizer='adam',\n              loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n              metrics=['accuracy'])\n\nprint(\"Model built successfully\")\nmodel.summary()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-06T16:04:22.033890Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-06T16:04:22.034515Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-06T16:04:27.174932Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-06T16:04:22.034474Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-06T16:04:27.174199Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"I0000 00:00:1775491463.751569      55 gpu_device.cc:2019] Created device /job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:GPU:0 with 13757 MB memory:  -> device: 0, name: Tesla T4, pci bus id: 0000:00:04.0, compute capability: 7.5\nI0000 00:00:1775491463.754480      55 gpu_device.cc:2019] Created device /job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:GPU:1 with 13757 MB memory:  -> device: 1, name: Tesla T4, pci bus id: 0000:00:05.0, compute capability: 7.5\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Downloading data from https://storage.googleapis.com/keras-applications/efficientnetb0_notop.h5\n\u001b[1m16705208/16705208\u001b[0m \u001b[32mв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m0s\u001b[0m 0us/step\nModel built successfully\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"\u001b[1mModel: \"sequential\"\u001b[0m\n","text/html":"<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'Deja